  <name>Pomerode</name>
  <summary>Minimal Pomodoro timer</summary>
  <description>
    <p>Pomerode is a sleek and user-friendly Pomodoro timer designed for elementary OS. Built with
      GTK4 and Libadwaita, it helps you maintain focus and productivity using the Pomodoro
      Technique.</p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Clean and Modern Interface. Follows elementary OS's design guidelines for a
        native look and feel</li>
      <li>Customizable Intervals. Adjust work duration, break duration, and long
        break settings</li>
      <li>Session Tracking Visual indicators show your progress through work
        intervals</li>
      <li>Smart Breaks. Automatically switches between focus sessions and breaks</li>
      <li>Autostart Option. Seamlessly transition between sessions with automatic
        start</li>
      <li>System Notifications. Get notified when sessions end or breaks begin</li>
      <li>Distraction-free. Minimal interface helps you stay focused on your tasks</li>
    </ul>
    <p>The Pomodoro Technique:</p>
    <p>The Pomodoro Technique is a time management method that uses a timer to break work into
      focused intervals (traditionally 25 minutes) separated by short breaks. After a set number of
      work intervals, you take a longer break. This helps maintain mental freshness and sustained
      concentration.</p>
  </description>

